Hey guys! It's been a VERY long time! My graduation is in 3 DAYS! So many things have changed since I've posted... Greg & I aren't together anymore! Man I hadn't updated in forever .. lemme think what all has happened ... Oh yeah the big thang my dad walked out right after my last post ..moved to Florida to live with some women he met on the net..my mom filed for divorce a few wks after he left..which meant she hadta pay for it..In March my cousin Misty died .. In April my parents divorce was final the same day we buried my favorite Uncle, Dale...April was also the prom I went to banquet with Will and of course I went to the Prom/Dance with Greg he looked so Hott in his tux....we had a good time then a bunch of ppl came to my house and partied ...May we had try outs for flag and of course I made it again lol ... finished our jr year won several awards (alg 11,Am. History,Chem) was usher at Sr class day and graduation....and the highlight of may Greg's Graduation...It was cute we were up in the stands and his mom ,leans over and says I hope he doesn't do anythang silly like some of them are,when he walks up to his seat he kisses his hand and blows me the biggest kiss ever lol ....afterwards was the party it was pretty cool ....this summer we have mostly just spent as much time as possible together between jobs and summer classes....He's going to PCC this fall so atleast he'll be close this year...The hardest part of life is death and once again that touched me the last few weeks.....We Sr's of 06 will be minus one classmate this yr as we begin the rest of our lives July 14th we lost Clint to an auto accident ....Clint was a sweetheart he could brighten anyones day and usually did mine ....It's gonna be hard this year not hearin Goodmorning Beautiful ....or damn you look good today ...the hardest part will we walkin across to get our diplomas and him not be there ... but I guess he'll always be in our hearts...William Clint Cardin Oct 5 1986-July 14 2005..R.I.P.......

Hey guys! Happy New Years! Greg & Zach came and got me Friday around 6:15. We went to John's. We all had a lot of fun! Usual new years stuff... talking, chatting, socializing, kissing.... it was great! ^_^ Some of us had more fun than others... ZACH! ^_~ Saturday we went to Matt's and they played PS2.... after I could actually keep food down and look presentable... Then we came back "home" and had supper with Greg's mom, Aunt Jennifer & Eric, Uncle John, and some guy named Kenneth. Zach finally crawled out of bed about the time Greg & I went back to bed... he slept a good 12 hours. I got up Sunday (this morning) about 11... it still felt like night-time! >_< I had a shower and then Greg fixed a PIZZA! My mom came & got me around 2... and  I have been home since then. It's back to the old grind... the nitty-gritty... wtf am I saying?! Want any more details...ask me! TTFN!

        <3 MeG                   *ILoVeGreG*

Hey everyone! I haven't been online in a LONG time. Christmas day I went to Gillett and stayed at my aunt's. Sunday was my cousin's wedding. I did most of the decorating. ^_^ Jeremy & Cerae loved it... so I obviously did very well! After the wedding I came back to Dewitt. Greg came to my house, and we opened presents! From him I got: Enchantment (perfume,) purple Snooz pillow, a red old navy hoodie, and a green long sleeve old navy tshirt. *i love Old Navy ^_^* From his mom and dad: Victoria Secret pj's, VS purse, VS lotion, spray, and shower gel. From Jennifer & Eric (his aunt and her fiance): Bath & Body Works foot care set and a bag. I got him: a red polo shirt, a brown Old Navy sweater, a button-up Chaps RL shirt, a necklace, and Spiderman 2 on DVD. I got stuff from other people too! My momma got me a purse, 2 pair of Abercrombie jeans, pair of Mudd jeans, and sweatshirts... other little stuff like makeup. I got $15 from my grandma. Earrings from Jessica.... a necklace and a buncha earrings from Christy... hand lotion and a jewelry box from my Aunt Loretta.

               Greg stayed from Sunday to Thursday. Sunday after we opened presents, we went back to Gillett to my aunt's to eat. Monday we watched movies and lounged around the house. Tuesday we went to Christy's to play dominoes ... her sister-in-law Kim was there and Greg tried to be nice, but mostly aggrivating her...lol. Wednesday we watched tv again and Thursday he left kinda early. He and Zach are gonna be back tonite to pick me up. Yeh... I'm going to a New Year's Eve "Party"... lol... umm at John's. Anyways... I'll be going now! TTFN!

          <3 MeG                *I LoVe Greg*

Heya people! My day was alright... night didn't start out so well. The ending looks good! I had Chinese tonight... it didn't make me feel so great. >_< Then... I ate ICE CREAM! I'm looking foward to the week being over. Greg just left not too long ago... I'm glad I got to talk to him twice today! ^_^ I saw him last night also... so my week isn't all bad. I didn't hafta go to school Monday, and Tuesday was Spanish Club trip to Little Rock to a Mexican Ballet and then to Casa Viva!!

     I'm glad several people are so understanding... you really mean a lot to me! I have had so much happen to me in the last year... Greg's made it easier to get through all of it. I've had the cancer scare, my uncle committing suicide, my dad is fixing to walk out on us, people are constantly turning against me, and school is hell. I know I brag on Greg a lot, but he doesn't get all the credit due... he and my mom have been there for me the whole time. There were several other people there supporting me also, but those two have helped me so much. I know I couldn't have done it all without them. ^_^ I've expected it out of my mom... but Greg is just amazing! OH... and also my little rascal of a sister has been a ... umm... someone to make me laugh! ^_~ heeeheee! No one else but her would suggest to go swimming OUTSIDE in NOVEMBER!! We may fight like dogs and cats, but I love my little monkey! ^_~

      I need to get to bed ... I'll post sometime, maybe next week! lol! Latah, Adios, Chao, Hasta Luega, Hasta manana, GOODBYE! <3

You Might Be Addicted To Live Journal If... If you can't access the site, you have a minor freak out - and a major case of hitting reload.

You found yourself composing journal entries during dates, movies, even sex!

When you're out, you suddenly think of a witty reply to a comment somebody made to you... several days ago.
 
You actually call it LJ and not Livejournal. Check.

You've downloaded some sort of LJ program which has only the purpose of making entries easier to write without going on the site manually.

You consider it a great offense if someone deletes you off their friend's list.

The first thing you do every day when you go online is check your friends journals - even before checking your email.

You actually paid money for a few extra pictures with a full account when you could actually just alternate pics when you want to for your screen icons.

When your friends ask what's new, you get mad at them because you already wrote it in your LJ and they didn't check it yet.

You have put more time into LJ than all your assignments for the semester.

You have more friends on LJ than in real life.

You've met at least 50% of your LJ friends.

You can't seem to call your friends by their real names - only LJ names will do.

You've fallen in love with someone you met on LJ.

You have posted about a party or get together on your LJ... and random strangers showed up.

You are guilty of traveling more than an hour to meet someone with LiveJournal. (Extra points for traveling five hours or more)

You've written a protected entry about one of your LiveJournal friends. (Extra points if they eventually found out about it)

You have written posts to notify people you're going to sleep.

You talk about your LJ friends to your real life friends all the time... like they're a part of your group.

You've created a LJ community, and people actually post in it.

You've been recognized in real live by a fellow LJ'er.

You have friended someone because of their LiveJournal icon.

You have "pity friends" on your list, who you would defriend if you could.

You've pimped one of your friends on journal, trying to get people to friend him / her.

Instead of doing research, you post difficult questions on your LiveJournal.

Your pets all have their own LiveJournals.

You know, right now, how many people have friended you (without peeking).

You've stopped being friends with someone in real life because of something they've said on LJ.

You're guilty of posting sexy or nude pictures to get more people to friend you.

You have consoled yourself after a horrible day thinking "At least this will make a great LJ post"

You're jealous of people who have more friends and / or comments than you.

You have written a really great, solid post - only to be disappointed by the lack of good comments.

You're guilty of commenting excessively to get more traffic to your journal.

You've deleted a post a few minutes (or hours) after you've written it, because it seemed lame in retro spect.

You give shout outs to all your LJ friends on their birthdays.

You have an additional, secret journal that hardly anyone knows about.

You've broken up with someone - or ended a friendship - soley via LiveJournal.

You have gotten mean anonymous comments (bonus points for figuring out who it was via their IP)

You've been reported (or reported someone) to LJ Abuse.

You've been featured on LJ Drama.

You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends who are LJ addicts
